newsitem.title: USA: U.S. jet falls with NYMEX, diffs ease in Gulf.
newsitem.headline: U.S. jet falls with NYMEX, diffs ease in Gulf.

text.p: U.S. jet fuel prices fell as much as one cent Wednesday amid lower NYMEX futures and weaker diffs in the Gulf Coast, players said.

Gulf Coast aviation-quality 54-grade was sold for 1.70 cents above September heat, 0.30 cent weaker than Tuesday diffs. Low sulfur 55-grade was offered at a 0.40 cent premium to 54-grade, traders said.
"A few refiners who were buying are not there now. And the arb window seems to be closing to the West Coast so there's less of a market there," one Gulf trader said.
He added that unexpectedly bearish EIA distillate data released Wednesday also helped weaken Gulf diffs.
Prompt New York Harbor 54-grade was offered at 4.75 cents over the print, stable with Tuesday, traders said.
